        <num>36-8-7</num>
        <content>
          <p>Upon the election or appointment of county police, the county governing authority shall make rules and regulations for the conduct, management, and control of such county police and shall, from time to time, enlarge, modify, or change such rules and regulations as its discretion may dictate.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1909, p. 156, ยง 5; Civil Code 1910, ยง 853; Ga. L. 1914, p. 142, ยง 5; Code 1933, ยง 23-1405.)</p>
